in  he joined the commodities trading firm j aron  co which was later acquired by goldman as a precious metals salesman in its london office blankfein managed or comanaged the goldman sachs currency and commodities division from  to  he served as vice chairman from april  until january  and was in charge of the fixed income currency and commodities division ficc and equities division blankfein has served as chairman and chief executive officer since  he earned a total of  million in  as one of the highestpaid executives on wall street his bonus reflected the performance of goldman sachs which reported record net earnings of  billion the compensation included a cash bonus of  million with the rest paid in stock and options while ceo of goldman sachs group in  blankfein earned a total compensation of  which included a base salary of  a cash bonus of  stocks granted of  and options granted of  he received us million in salary and bonuses in  which was slightly down from the us million he earned in  from goldman sachs in  the financial times named blankfein its  person of the year stating his bank has stuck to its strengths unashamedly taken advantage of the low interest rates and diminished competition resulting from the crisis to make big trading profits on january   blankfein testified before the financial crisis inquiry commission that he considered goldman sachss role as primarily a market maker not a creator of the product ie subprime mortgagerelated securities blankfein testified before congress in april  at a hearing of the senate permanent subcommittee on investigations he said that goldman sachs had no moral or legal obligation to inform its clients it was betting against the products which they were buying from goldman sachs because it was not acting in a fiduciary role the company was sued on april   by the sec for the fraudulent selling of a synthetic cdo tied to subprime mortgages with blankfein at the helm goldman has also been criticized by lawmakers and pundits for issues from its pay practices to its role in helping greece mask the size of its debts in april  a permanent subcommittee on investigations report accused goldman sachs of misleading clients about complex mortgagerelated investments in  and senator carl levin alleged that blankfein misled congress though no perjury charges have been brought against blankfein in august of the same year goldman confirmed that blankfein had hired highprofile defense lawyer reid weingarten who had previously represented executives including former worldcom ceo bernard ebbers and former enron accounting officer richard causey two months later in november  blankfein was listed as  on forbes magazines list of the worlds most powerful people in march  a former goldman executive greg smith wrote an oped for the new york times titled why i am leaving goldman sachs in which he heavily criticized the firms top leadership and blankfein in particular smiths oped was criticized by many particularly because he worked at goldman for  years before deciding to quit due to moral objections politicsedit with regard to his personal political views blankfein has described himself as a registered democrat and a rockefeller republican  conservative on fiscal issues and more liberal on social issues blankfein contributes to mostly democratic party candidates and donated  to democratic party candidate hillary clinton in  he is a supporter of gay marriage and has been a spokesman for the human rights campaign in may  blankfein stated that his stance led goldman sachs to lose some clients blankfein has visited the white house  times as of january  in  he contributed to the senate reelection campaigns for the republicans rob portman and roy blunt after  democratic presidential candidate bernie sanders in january  named blankfein as an example of corporate greed blankfein responded that sanders campaign had the potential to be a dangerous moment on april   he recommended guidelines to overhaul executive compensation according to the new york times he said that lessons from the global financial crisis included the need to apply basic standards to how we compensate people in our industry in november  he declared in an interview as a banker im doing gods work several days later he indicated that he regretted that remark and said he had intended it as a joke he also apologized on behalf of goldman sachs to the public for unspecified things that were clearly wrong and have reason to regret and which contributed to the financial and economic crisis the firm announced a  small businesses initiative committing  million to aid american small businesses on july   he commented about the effect of the libor scandal on the financial system there was this huge hole to dig out of in terms of getting trust back and now its just that much deeper  the same day he met jack lew president barack obamas chief of staff and over lunch at the economic club of washington was asked whether he had any aspiration to go into government like predecessors hank paulson and robert rubin i have aspirations to be desired he replied on june   blankfein posted his first ever tweet despite joining the social media service in  he condemned president trumps withdrawal from the paris accord saying todays decision is a setback for the environment and for the uss leadership position in the world parisagreement philanthropyedit blankfein formerly served on the board of trustees of the robin hood foundation a charitable organization whose goal is to alleviate poverty in new york he serves on the board of directors of the partnership for new york city and on the board of overseers of the weill cornell medical college personal lifeedit blankfein is married to laura jacobs an attorney and the daughter of norman s jacobs the editorinchief of the foreign policy association publications the couple have two sons alexander and jonathan and a daughter rachel on september   goldman sachs released a statement saying blankfein had been diagnosed with a highly treatable form of lymphoma he received a treatment of chemotherapy by october  he explained he was cured blankfein and his wife reside primarily in manhattans upper west side but they also maintain a home in bridgehampton new york as well as another house set on  acres in sagaponack new york referencesedit  moore michael roux pamela  july  lloyd blankfein is now a billionaire bloombergcom bloomberg lp retrieved  january    moore james april   lloyd blankfein the prince of casino capitalism the independent london retrieved april     jacobson mark september   the land that time and money forgot new york retrieved september     a b gapper john master of risk who did gods work for goldman sachs but won it little love financial times retrieved december    a b laura jacobs engaged to lloyd c blankfein the new york times may   retrieved may     a b c d e f james nye inside goldman sachs ceo lloyd blankfeins new  million hamptons estatebought even though he still hasnt sold his other  million long island home the daily mail december    lloyd blankfein was a history major just sayin bloomberg january   retrieved may     lloyd blankfeins advice to interns — relax business insider october   retrieved may     a b the worlds most powerful people  lloyd blankfein forbes retrieved october     blankfein offers billionaire nba owners advice as stern exits bloomberg   a b lloyd c blankfein chairman and chief executive officer goldman sachs goldman sachs retrieved  july    ceo compensation for lloyd c blankfein  equilarcom  oran olivia goldman awards ceo blankfein  million in pay for  reuterscom reuters retrieved  january    cohan william d april  wall street executives from the financial crisis of  where are they now vanity fair retrieved march     goldman sachs ceo lloyd blankfein named financial times person of the year the huffington post retrieved december    kenney caitlin january   financial crisis inquiry commission day one npr   quin