fein has visited the white house  times as of january  in  he contributed to the senate reelection campaigns for the republicans rob portman and roy blunt after  democratic presidential candidate bernie sanders in january  named blankfein as an example of corporate greed blankfein responded that sanders campaign had the potential to be a dangerous moment on april   he recommended guidelines to overhaul executive compensation according to the new york times he said that lessons from the global financial crisis included the need to apply basic standards to how we compensate people in our industry in november  he declared in an interview as a banker im doing gods work several days later he indicated that he regretted that remark and said he had intended it as a joke he also apologized on behalf of goldman sachs to the public for unspecified things that were clearly wrong and have reason to regret and which contributed to the financial and economic crisis the firm announced a  small businesses initiative committing  million to aid american small businesses on july   he commented about the effect of the libor scandal on the financial system there was this huge hole to dig out of in terms of getting trust back and now its just that much deeper  the same day he met jack lew president barack obamas chief of staff and over lunch at the economic club of washington was asked whether he had any aspiration to go into government like predecessors hank paulson and robert rubin i have aspirations to be desired he replied on june   blankfein posted his first ever tweet despite joining the social media service in  he condemned president trumps withdrawal from the paris accord saying todays decision is a setback for the environment and for the uss leadership position in the world parisagreement philanthropyedit blankfein formerly served on the board of trustees of the robin hood foundation a charitable organization whose goal is to alleviate poverty in new york he serves on the board of directors of the partnership for new york city and on the board of overseers of the weill cornell medical college personal lifeedit blankfein is married to laura jacobs an attorney and the daughter of norman s jacobs the editorinchief of the foreign policy association publications the couple have two sons alexander and jonathan and a daughter rachel on september   goldman sachs released a statement saying blankfein had been diagnosed with a highly treatable form of lymphoma he received a treatment of chemotherapy by october  he explained he was cured blankfein and his wife reside primarily in manhattans upper west side but they also maintain a home in bridgehampton new york as well as another house set on  acres in sagaponack new york referencesedit  moore michael roux pamela  july  lloyd blankfein is now a billionaire bloombergcom bloomberg lp retrieved  january    moore james april   lloyd blankfein the prince of casino capitalism the independent london retrieved april     jacobson mark september   the land that time and money forgot new york retrieved september     a b gapper john master of risk who did gods work for goldman sachs but won it little love financial times retrieved december    a b laura jacobs engaged to lloyd c blankfein the new york times may   retrieved may     a b c d e f james nye inside goldman sachs ceo lloyd blankfeins new  million hamptons estatebought even though he still hasnt sold his other  million long island home the daily mail december    lloyd blankfein was a history major just sayin bloomberg january   retrieved may     lloyd blankfeins advice to interns — relax business insider october   retrieved may     a b the worlds most powerful people  lloyd blankfein forbes retrieved october     blankfein offers billionaire nba owners advice as stern exits bloomberg   a b lloyd c blankfein chairman and chief executive officer goldman sachs goldman sachs retrieved  july    ceo compensation for lloyd c blankfein  equilarcom  oran olivia go