 who we are leadership executive officers lloyd c blankfein chairman and chief executive officer lloyd blankfein has been the chairman and chief executive officer of the goldman sachs group inc since june  and a director since april  he serves as a member of the goldman sachs management committee and board of directors previously he had been the firm’s president and chief operating officer and prior to that from april  until january  he was a vice chairman of goldman sachs with management responsibility for goldman sachs’ fixed income currency and commodities division ficc and equities division prior to becoming a vice chairman he had served as cohead of ficc since its formation in  from  to  he headed or coheaded the currency and commodities division mr blankfein is not currently on the board of any public company other than goldman sachs he is affiliated with certain nonprofit organizations including as a member of the dean’s advisory board at harvard law school the board of dean’s advisors of harvard business school the dean’s council of harvard university the advisory board of the tsinghua university school of economics and management the board of overseers of weill cornell medical college and the board of the partnership for new york city featured content business principles and standards business principles and our commitment to clients our business principles define our fundamental expectations for the way we should interact with our clients manage our business and attract retain and motivate our employees learn more citizenship  environmental social and governance report our environmental social and governance report highlights our commitment to sustainability and describes our work on behalf of our clients and the communities we seek to serve explore report goldman sachs  podcast exchanges at goldman sachs  episode  a conversation with lloyd blankfein search twitter goldmansachs gscareers gskwomen gsksmallbiz linkedin gplus youtube our thinking podcast exch